 possibly can, Ean will get another bonus point added to his roll in addition to his level bonus point(s), to increase his odds of getting the drop, but not change the "one default" rule that I started the raid under)<br>(EDIT 6/1:As for the rest of the royal family's epic loot, it will be randomed off to attendees needing the drops.  Level bonuses will apply here also, with those at this stage of epic getting one point bonuses to their level bonus point(s).  This edit is in place due to Kdor's post that made me realise I was excluding some from completion due to level conflicts.)<br><br>Note: It is not my intention to keep the lower levels out of the race for their epic, but i do think the higher the level you are, the more important that it becomes to have your epic. <br>(EDIT 6/1: if Royals loot is the next step in your epic, rather than claiming the loot out of sequence, please post here, so that I may include your bonus points on the random)<br><br>Necessities:<br>55+ monk with "experience" pulling on a royals raid<br>55+ enc (the higher the better, but CII, and ability to mez are crucial)<br>55+ shaman for slows and debuffs<br>58-60 warr (MA)<br>58-60 warr (SA)<br>56+ cleric (epic if possible) for fast recovery if there is a wipe out (which Chardok is famous for)<br>55+ rogue (not only as a damage dealer and scout, but also CR specialist, should things get outta hand)<br><br>I need nukes, melees, alt healers, melees, buffers/debuffers, melees and finally...melees.  I would encourage a 55+ necro to show up also, to assist with CR.<br><br>Minimum preferred level for this is 53+ for all members (and that is stretching it to the lowest point).  Many of the MoBs past the BK are 55+, so the higher the better.<br>I want to take 5 full groups.  Less than that is asking for trouble, more is better, but 5 is optimal.<br><br>Plan of action:  <br>1 hour setup and clear to the castle; <br>1 hour move to royals; <br>4 hour camp on royals for 2 full spawn cycles.<br><br>Please sign up here and I will update this post every few days as people sign up.<br>Please be on time, or early.  <br>Meeting point is the zone in inside Chardok.<br>Be ready to fight, be ready to win, be ready to move.<br>I suggest doing a fresh restart of your computer and modem prior to logging in, as that is most times the case of initial LDs.  <br>Cleric/enc will be provided 1 stack of peridots each once inside Chardok.<br>Coffins will be provided, should there be a need.<br>Loot will be randomed in BW, outside of Chardok after the raid is finished. <br><br>My first rule of raiding is...USE ASSIST!!!<br>My second rule is ....WAIT FOR THE MA TO CALL ASSIST!!!<br><br>I donot stand for blatant disregard to these 2 trivial, well-known, common sense rules.  Go show off for the guys/girls in some other zone, cause I donot want that crap on my raids.<br><br>Other than that, it should be fun, informative, profitable and the xp there is awesome. <p><img src="http://rumandmonkey.com/widgets/tests/giantrobot/gigantor.jpg" width="200" height="150"><br><a href="http://rumandmonkey.com/widgets/tests/giantrobot/">Which Colossal Death Robot Are <i>You</i>?</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=196142">Dalnarek Lifeinstater</a><br>Battle Lord, officer and priest of Dogmatic Crucible<br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/udalnareklifeinstater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DalnarekLifeinstater</A> at: 5/31/02 11:20:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/ueanelarstoneheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eanelar StoneHeart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/31/02 11:33:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2403.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span